text: Salina is a genus of elongate-bodied springtails in the family Paronellidae. There are about five described species in Salina. ==Species== * Salina banksi Macgillivray, 1894 * Salina beta Christiansen & Bellinger, 1980 * Salina celebensis (Schaeffer, 1898) * Salina mulcahyae Christiansen & Bellinger, 1980 * Salina trilobata Mills, 1932 ==References== Category:Hexapoda
title: Salina (springtail)
